headline: Why Moderna Stock Was So Healthy This Week
summary: The company was pleased to report the findings of a late-stage clinical trial of its advanced flu vaccine.  Moderna (NASDAQ: MRNA), the next-generation healthcare company most famous for developing the Spikevax coronavirus vaccine, was an uncharacteristically popular stock.  On Monday, Moderna published the results of a late-stage study of mRNA-1010, its seasonal flu vaccine.
